[code=java5]public class Collatz {

	private int iterations = 0;

	private Collatz(String args[]) {
		collatz(Integer.parseInt(args[0]));
		System.out.println("Iterations to solve: "+iterations);
	}

	private void collatz(int n) {
		System.out.println(n);
		if(n > 1) {
			collatz(n%2==0?n/2:3*n+1);
			iterations++;
		}
	}

	public static void main(String args[]) {
		if(args.length > 0)
			new Collatz(args);
		else
			System.out.println("Usage: java Collatz <integer>");
	}

}

[/code]

Simple application to work out how many iterations are needed to get to the number 1 from the Integer given at runtime using the [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collatz_conjecture]Collatz Conjecture[/url].
